data.description: New and Improved! Take advantage of the 2/1 buy-down rates starting as low as 5.625 with our preferred lender. Don’t miss out on an amazing opportunity to get into this beautifully appointed and stunning move-in ready home within a desirable swim/tennis community in an accessible Kennesaw location with great schools. Step in from the front porch through the front door and you’ll be welcomed by soaring ceilings in the 2 -story foyer and the 2-story great room. Warm freshly refinished hardwood floors extend throughout the main level including the separate dining room, the living room, and the dedicated office space with French doors.   A well-maintained home featuring recent updates, including new carpeting on the entire second floor. The kitchen comes complete with newer cabinets, Quartz counters, Stainless appliances with a double oven, separate cooktop, new lighting, and a kitchen island. The breakfast area is in clear view of the 2-story family room which brings in lots of natural lighting through the walls of windows. The open concept floorplan provides the ideal space for entertaining guests or simply relaxing with your loved ones.  The second floor presents the large primary suite in ultimate luxury, comfort, and relaxation. Featuring huge walk-in his and her closets, a luxurious recently remodeled bath with double vanities with quartz counter tops, an extended shower with double shower heads and new modern finishes and fixtures. An additional finished space behind “his”-closet could be used as an office or customized and used as additional closet space. The secondary bedrooms have a shared hallway bathroom for two bedrooms and an additional spacious room with a private bath and walk-in closet.   Ideal for multi-generational living, this home features a finished terrace level equipped with a fully functioning kitchen, a bedroom, a bathroom with a steam shower, custom built-ins, and surround sound system. There is enough room for a game room, an office or a gym and this area can be accessed from the exterior through a side entry door.  The home also has upgraded plumbing with Pex pipes and a water sensor system, newer roofing, and new garage doors completes the choice for your new home. The yard is fully fenced-in for complete privacy.  This is a great home with excellent features peacefully situated next to a quiet cul-de-sac. Visit today and make this your new home
